              <div class="featuretext span12 light light">
                Whether it’s a film, short, music video or any other piece of creative content, its all a project. Defining what your project is becomes the first step for any content creator.
<br><br>
								A lot of people toss ideas around in their head and are not sure where to start.  We’ve all been there.  You might have a rough concept mapped out, a script outline, or gigabytes of rough footage that needs to be cut.  Taking your idea to reality is the first step, but it also can be an incredibly emotional and difficult plunge to take.
<br><br>
								There are a lot of things you might be unsure of or what to risk on your project.  As you ask yourself tough questions, remember why are you doing this.  If your goal is to shed light on a difficult topic, make money, or you just simply love film...take the leap and create a project! We built filmmo with the same counter-culture mentality as the artists we serve. We get that making a film is an intense and deeply personal experience, and you do it because of how it makes you feel.  At filmmo, we exist to make your film a reality and we want to help you meet the people that will make your film great.       
								<br><br>
								<blockquote class="pull-right">
								  <i>You can't connect the dots looking forward; you can only connect them looking backwards. So you have to trust that the dots will somehow connect in your future. You have to trust in something - your gut, destiny, life, karma, whatever. This approach has never let me down, and it has made all the difference in my life.</i>
								  <small>Steve Jobs</small>
								</blockquote>
								<br><br>
								Imagine the stories, the things you’ll learn, all the fantastic interactions you’ll have with people as you film.  As hard as it may be in an early stage, try to keep your goals simple. filmmo works best when there is a basic goal and you use the people you bring on to help you refine the goal to get you there. Don’t be afraid to pivot, some of the greatest films are made through a series of serendipitous and unforeseen events.
